By Campbell
HOUSE BILL 1057
By Mitchell
AN ACT to amend Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 4;
Title 40 and Title 41, relative to The Parole
Advancement and Reintegration Act.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SECTION 1. This act is known and may be cited as "The Parole Advancement and
Reintegration Act."
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 40, Chapter 28, Part 6, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
(a) The department shall develop an early parole termination program for
parolees who have:
(1) Maintained stable and verifiable employment for at least six (6)
consecutive months;
(2) Remained law-abiding and free of any violations or arrests while on
parole; and
(3) Completed all rehabilitation and treatment programs as required by
the sentencing court and the department.
(b) The program must:
(1) Include an earned time credit system that is substantially similar to
the sentence reduction credits available to inmates under ยง 41-21-236, and
provide for a gradual reduction of supervision with a goal of full discharge from
parole after five (5) years in the program;
(2) Require parolees to be assessed twice a year as to eligibility for
participation in the program; and
